Complaint regarding alleged interference in recruitment and selection processes  24 January 2022 The Public Service Commission (PSC) has received a complaint, lodged by Dr Leon Schreiber, Member of Parliament, requesting a formal investigation into the alleged interference of the Cadre Deployment Committee of the African National Congress into Public Service appointments. The PSC is currently assessing the complaint, including the question of the PSCâ€™s legal mandate to investigate such complaint in order to determine the appropriate action to take in the matter. Issued by Richard Sizani, Chairperson, Public Service Commission, 25 January 2022